title: after upgrade to v2.2, can't import deeplabcut
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

Had a working version of deeplabcut (v1.9). After upgrading to v2.2, running `import deeplabcut` raises error

```
2022-09-08 16:21:22.297155: W tensorflow/stream_executor/platform/default/dso_loader.cc:64] Could not load dynamic library 'cudart64_110.dll'; dlerror: cudart64_110.dll not found
2022-09-08 16:21:22.304440: I tensorflow/stream_executor/cuda/cudart_stub.cc:29] Ignore above cudart dlerror if you do not have a GPU set up on your machine.
...
AttributeError: module 'deeplabcut' has no attribute 'pose_estimation_tensorflow'
```

### Operating System

Windows 10

### DeepLabCut version

dlc version 2.2.0.6

### DeepLabCut mode

multi animal

### Device type

gpu

### Steps To Reproduce

start anaconda prompt
conda activate dlc-windowsGPU
pip install --upgrade deeplabcut
ipython
import deeplabcut
